The paper focuses on improving the performance of human pose estimation through data processing, which is a common problem in computer vision (cs.CV) and machine learning (cs.LG). The authors also propose a principled approach to tackle this problem, which involves formulating a new strategy for data processing, indicating a focus on artificial intelligence (cs.AI). Additionally, the paper involves quantitative analyses, which suggests a potential fit for multimedia (cs.MM) and neural and evolutionary computing (cs.NE) sub-categories.
